<section id="about" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); background:#0c0c0e;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px; margin:0 auto; padding:104px 32px;" class="section-pad">
    <div class="two-col" style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1.05fr; gap:72px; align-items:start;">
      <!-- Left: copy -->
      <div>
        <div
          data-reveal
          style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; letter-spacing:0.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:20px;"
        >
          Why me
        </div>
        <h2
          data-reveal
          style="font-weight:600; font-size:36px; line-height:1.14; letter-spacing:-0.025em; margin:0 0 22px; color:#fafafa;"
        >
          An engineer who actually wants to do the people part.
        </h2>
        <p data-reveal style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.7; color:#9a9a9a; margin:0 0 18px;">
          I've spent six years building production frontends in React and TypeScript, including
          frontend platform work, so I can read your API and SDK the way your engineers do. The
          technical fluency is real.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.7; color:#9a9a9a; margin:0 0 30px;">
          The difference is that I genuinely want the public-facing, relational work most engineers
          avoid: the writing, the videos, the community, the patient support that makes developers
          feel taken care of. That combination is rare, and it's the whole point.
        </p>
        <div
          data-reveal
          style="border-left:2px solid var(--accent); padding:4px 0 4px 20px;"
        >
          <p
            style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.6; color:#c4c4c4; margin:0 0 10px; font-style:italic;"
          >
            I've been the confused developer at 1am staring at a half-documented endpoint. I build
            the experience I wish I'd had, and I like doing it in public.
          </p>
          <div style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:var(--accent);">
            Sarah
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: credentials -->
      <div data-reveal style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">
        <div
          style="display:flex; gap:18px; padding:22px 0; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);"
        >
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; color:var(--accent); width:30px; flex:none;"
            >01</span
          >
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px; color:#ededed; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:4px;">
              Six years of production React &amp; TypeScript
            </div>
            <div style="font-size:14.5px; color:#8b8b8b; line-height:1.55;">
              Real engineering, shipped in production over years — not hobby projects.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          style="display:flex; gap:18px; padding:22px 0; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);"
        >
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; color:var(--accent); width:30px; flex:none;"
            >02</span
          >
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px; color:#ededed; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:4px;">
              I read the code and the API
            </div>
            <div style="font-size:14.5px; color:#8b8b8b; line-height:1.55;">
              Frontend platform background means I understand what your developers are actually
              hitting, not just what the docs say they should hit.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          style="display:flex; gap:18px; padding:22px 0; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);"
        >
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; color:var(--accent); width:30px; flex:none;"
            >03</span
          >
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px; color:#ededed; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:4px;">
              Content, video &amp; community are the job I want
            </div>
            <div style="font-size:14.5px; color:#8b8b8b; line-height:1.55;">
              The outgoing, public-facing work is the part of this job I most look forward to, not
              the part I'm tolerating to stay employed.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="display:flex; gap:18px; padding:22px 0;">
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; color:var(--accent); width:30px; flex:none;"
            >04</span
          >
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px; color:#ededed; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:4px;">
              Empathy for the first-run experience
            </div>
            <div style="font-size:14.5px; color:#8b8b8b; line-height:1.55;">
              Because I've debugged it myself, frustrated, at the wrong hour.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
